		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Especially because I'm sitting on a half-done NROM-128 game, waiting for an excuse to finish it.</div>
<br />Like I said, there is no way to fully control whether existing code will be used, but even if you have a suitably small game that still has to be finished at least you will spend the time making the program as good as possible, instead of using the time to generate a lot of data, so I think 32KB is good either way.
<br />
<br />Personally I think that 16KB is a bit to restrictive, and is only really suitable for very repetitive games where the difference between levels is just the difficulty, without many layout changes.

		

